@otaviobp I'm thinking of going with another approach (slightly) of ignoring mix state when version != get_current_version(NULL), effectively disallowing version-specific verification against local mixes.
This does not, and is not intended to, fix the overall issue of messy mixer integration. We need a way to allow users to get back to upstream and I think this is the fastest way to do it.
There is a larger issue that the mixer state is messy and there are a couple of different indicators for swupd to figure out if it is on a mix or not. This definitely needs to be cleaned up and if you have ideas for a cleaner architecture I'd love to see that proposal.

