@bryteise After this PR signature verification for latest file is going to be completely enforced. If signature is missing or incorrect, any swupd operation will be aborted. If user wants to proceed there's a new flag --nosigcheck-latest that will ignore latest signature, but continue to check Manifests, so it's safer than --nosigcheck.
On an update, if there is a mirror set we always check if the mirror is out of sync with upstream. In the case where signature for mirror is invalid or missing, we consider the mirror out of sync and update will proceed using the default url (upstream).
